**What changed in `scripts/append_terminal_state_events.py`:**

1. **`lifecycle_for_scope()` (line 92):** `SessionStarted` added alongside `RunStarted` in both the session-run detection set and the non-session lifecycle branches. `SessionStarted` events are now counted as lifecycle starts, added to `run_started` or `session_run_started` depending on `is_session_run()`, and increment `lifecycle_start_count`.

2. **`find_stale_orphaned_runs()` (line 198):** Same treatment — `SessionStarted` recognized identically to `RunStarted` in both the session-run and non-session branches. Docstring updated to mention both event types.

**New tests (all passing):**
• `test_lifecycle_for_scope_session_started_as_lifecycle_start` — `SessionStarted` alone (no `RunStarted`) counts as a lifecycle start and correctly shows the run as open
• `test_lifecycle_for_scope_session_started_session_scope` — `SessionStarted` with `phase=session` is tracked as a session run
• `test_find_stale_orphaned_runs_session_started` — `SessionStarted` + `ModelCallStarted` but no `RunCompleted` is detected as an orphan
• `test_find_stale_orphaned_runs_session_started_completed` — `SessionStarted` + `RunCompleted` is correctly not an orphan

